    <title>Ridiculously Good Olive Oil Dip!</title>

    <comment></comment>
    <thumbnail>../images/placeholder.png</thumbnail>
    <image></image>
    <category></category>
    <yield></yield>
    <prepTime></prepTime>
    <cookTime></cookTime>
    



    <ingredient>2 garlic cloves crushed</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 TBsp capers finely chopped</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/2 teaspoon dried oregano</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 TBsp fresh rosemary finely chopped</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 teaspoons fresh thyme finely chopped</ingredient>
    <ingredient>3 TBsp finely grated Parmesan cheese</ingredient>
    <ingredient>salt and cracked pepper to taste</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/2 cup good quality extra-virgin olive oil</ingredient>
    <ingredient>pepper flakes (optional)</ingredient>
    <ingredient>Crusty bread to serve</ingredient>

    <step>
Place all ingredients in a jar and shake well.  Serve spread out on a flat plate with crusty bread.  Alternatively you can mix all ingredients except olive oil and make two mounds on a plate, then pour olive oil around mounds.  Serve with crusty bread or crackers.
    </step>
</recipe>